48:59.161 --> 49:02.966
We mark and make sacred the ordinary occasions in our lives that are about us.

49:03.066 --> 49:05.869
Graduation, retirements, awards.

49:05.889 --> 49:09.714
We charge our accomplishments with reference, and that's all well and good.

49:10.882 --> 49:18.254
In all honesty, I do believe that you are sacred, you are set apart, you are imbued with the image of God, and you are worth making sacred and celebrating.

49:19.336 --> 49:28.251
But Jesus also says that the way to live fullest is not by turning my focus back on myself.

49:29.693 --> 49:30.715
It's the opposite of that.

49:32.077 --> 49:37.266
It's by losing myself in a cruciform sacrificial love for the other people who are in my life today.

49:38.434 --> 49:40.677
Jesus has lose your life, lay all of it down.

49:41.679 --> 49:50.212
And the Psalms prayed authentically, they are a ritual of submitting myself to a greater authority, of losing myself.

49:51.894 --> 49:56.301
An authority whose character summarized in a single word is love.

49:58.143 --> 50:02.850
That he might remake my character summarized in that same word.

50:03.752 --> 50:04.212
Love.

50:05.434 --> 50:08.018
Why don't we stand, we'll respond together.

50:08.290 --> 50:16.984
Thanks for joining the Bridgestown family as we engage in this teaching series.

50:17.725 --> 50:23.675
To learn more about the life of our church and how you can get involved, visit bridgestown.church.com.

50:24.436 --> 50:32.690
If you're interested in contributing financially to Bridgestown Church and to our ministry, you can do that at bridgestown.church.gov.

50:33.218 --> 50:42.610
Wherever you're joining us from, we hope this resource blesses you and encourages you to be with Jesus, become like Jesus, and do what Jesus did.

